figgy.title: Resource Metadata Preservation Inline Running Causes Inaccurate Stored MD5 Checksums
Local fixity only runs on primary file

comments.body:
Eliot and I looked at this together, and found the following things:

* We don't calculate local checksums for IntermediateFiles. Characterization only runs on primary_file, and then the derivative services look at intermediate after that.
* Cloud preservation re-generates the checksum for every binary node it preserves the first time, which includes intermediate nodes. This means the cloud has a checksum value for preserved intermediate files, and is able to check that.

To close this ticket we'd have to do the following:

* Calculate checksums for intermediate files during characterization (maybe re-queue characterization when appending an intermediate file?)
* We'd have to run characterization on every FileSet that has an intermediate file.
* We'd have to store the `child_id` for local fixity events as the FileMetadata ID it ran against (or change the meaning of a failed local fixity check to be "one of the binary files failed figure it out")
* If we do the above, we'd have to re-run local fixity on everything again. We'd also have to delete all the old local fixity events.

@tpendragon If you add a folder, it won't preserve until it's marked "complete", no matter the state of the parent box. Feels OK to me to only trigger preservation on a Folder once it's marked complete, but I may not know the use cases.
@eliotjordan If I add a folder to an all_in_production box does it behave as if it's complete or nah?
@tpendragon It does not until you mark it complete.

Do we really want to change the current state of Ephemera Preservation?

The current situation:
1. EphemeraProjects always preserve. Just metadata, no state.
2. EphemeraBoxes always preserve. Just metadata.
3. EphemeraFolders preserve when they are marked "complete"
4. Marking an EphemeraBox as "all_in_production" will propagate the "complete" state to all folders and they will preserve themselves.

This all seems fine to me. There are many Boxes in a non "all_in_production" state and it is probably a good idea for Folders to be preserved when complete despite the state of the Box.
The current state has evolved a lot! Have you checked the preservation store to make sure this all happens? I wasn't aware 4 was true, for instance.
@tpendragon I'm pushing up a PR that adds tests for 2 and 4.

@tpendragon Pretty sure that this is covering 4:
https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/pull/5726/files#diff-e853398d3115ab6b67081bc92741745dc2c7c39c66bd78c205381f1ea4b45c30R58

@eliotjordan What happens to folders added to all_in_production boxes after it's marked? Maybe that doesn't happen - does it @kelea99 ?

Edit: Also, good work on those tests! That's awesome!
